Come watch the SPARK Pitch Contest! Support your friends and community members, help build excitement for a particular solution through audience engagement, or satisfy your curiosity about the social innovation solutions developed by this year’s SPARK Challenge teams.


Students taking the SPARK Challenge course this spring will work with a community partner to innovate a solution to a local social challenge.&#160;


Teams competing in the SPARK Pitch Contest will have about 10 minutes each to summarize their challenge and solution, pitch the idea to the audience, explain their budget, and convince the judges that their solution should win implementation funding. Judges may ask questions for clarification and may offer constructive feedback to the team.&#160;


We hope to see you there!&#160;

